, was elected as the new Bishop of Kurunegala.\n\n== List of bishops==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width:95%;\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"2\"\n\n|-\n! colspan=\"5\" style=\"background-color: #7F1734; color: white;\" | Bishops of Kurunegala\n\n|-\n! style=\"background-color: #D4B1BB; width: 5%;\" | From\n! style=\"background-color: #D4B1BB; width: 5%;\" | Until\n! style=\"background-color: #D4B1BB; width: 16%;\" | Incumbent\n! style=\"background-color: #D4B1BB; width: 20%;\" | Notes\n\n|-\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" | 1950\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" | 1962\n|'''[[Lakdasa De Mel]]'''\n|first Bishop of Kurunegala, installed on 2 February 1950; installed in May 1962 as [[Metropolitan Bishop]] of India, Pakistan, Burma and Ceylon\n\n|-\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" | 1962\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" | 1983\n|'''[[Lakshman Wickremasinghe]]'''\n|one of the youngest [[bishop]]s in the [[Anglican Communion]]\n\n|-\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" | 1983\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" | 2000\n|'''[[Andrew Kumarage]]''' \n|\n\n|-\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" | 2000\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" | 2010\n|'''[[Kumara Illangasinghe]]''' \n|\n\n|-\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" | 2010\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" | 2015\n|'''[[Shantha Francis]]''' \n|first [[Tamil people|Tamil]] bishop, resigned in January 2015\n\n|-\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" | 2015\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" | 2017\n| colspan=3 | vacant\n\n|-\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" | 2018\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" | present\n|'''[[Keerthisiri Fernando]]''' \n|\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Publications==\n* [https://archive.org/details/yearsinceylon00balduoft One hundred years in Ceylon, or, The centenary volume of the Church Missionary Society in Ceylon, 1818-1918 (1922) Author: Balding, John William] Madras: Printed at the Diocesan Press.\n* [https://openlibrary.org/b/OL18758914M/Church-of-Ceylon The Church of Ceylon - her faith and mission]